article.description: Ongwae's steal seals UL-Monroe's win over UL-Lafayette
article.headline: Ongwae's steal seals UL-Monroe's win over UL-Lafayette
article.linkText: Ongwae's steal seals UL-Monroe's win over UL-Lafayette
article.story: LAFAYETTE, La. -- Tylor Ongwae stole a floor-length pass, then hit 1 of 2 free throws with 1.2 seconds left to help Louisiana-Monroe hold off in-state rival Louisiana-Lafayette 57-55 on Monday night for its sixth straight win. Louisiana-Lafayette made eight straight free throws, during an 8-4 run, to cut its deficit to 56-55 with 38 seconds left. UL-Monroe's Justin Roberson missed the first of a one-and-one opportunity with 2.8 left and Ongwae intercepted a long pass to seal it. Ongwae finished with 13 points for UL-Monroe (12-6, 6-1 Sun Belt). Roberson had eight points, six rebounds and four assists. UL-Louisiana (10-8, 4-3) lost back-to-back home games after winning 12 straight at home. Shawn Long scored 19 points, grabbed nine rebounds and had three blocks for Louisiana-Lafayette. Devonta Walker added 15 points and also had nine rebounds. The Ragin' Cajuns converted 17 of 18 free throws, but were just 2 of 18 from distance.
